{
  "texts": [
    "Methods of EvaluationAlthough foundation models provide convenience in creating narrative visualizations, their widespread application faces some potential challenges.",
    "One major issue is the variability in how these models can be instructed, as different prompts can lead to divergent and unpredictable results of the process.",
    "Moreover, the presence of hallucinations, where models generate inaccurate or non-sensical content even in tasks as structured as visualization generation, further complicates their use [148].Recently, several studies have emerged to evaluate visualizations created by foundation models [7], [79], [129] through various human evaluations from various perspectives to identify their strengths and weaknesses.",
    "However, in practical applications, automated evaluation methods and a comprehensive set of metrics are necessary to evaluate the visualizations generated by these models effectively.",
    "For example, Podo et al. [148] proposed a conceptual framework called EvaLLM, which systematically dissects and models the evaluation of data visualizations generated by LLMs."
  ]
}